Canada%2C%20traveling%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20is%20virtually%20a%20non-issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-canada-from-us-pros-cons-heathcare-home-prices%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIf%20you're%20an%20American%20coming%20to%20Canada%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20can%20travel%20visa-free.%20Still%2C%20if%20you're%20planning%20to%20move%20here%20and%20be%20able%20to%20work%20here%2C%20that's%20another%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20visit%20for%20six%20months%20as%20long%20as%20you%20leave%20before%20the%20end%20of%20the%20six-month%20period.%20You%20can%20do%20that%20back%20and%20forth%20all%20the%20time%20%E2%80%94%20but%20you%20won't%20get%20access%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwe-moved-to-canada-not-perfect-but-prefer-over-us-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocial%20system%20and%20healthcare%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20friends%2C%20who%20used%20to%20live%20in%20Chicago%2C%20moved%20to%20California%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe're%20going%20to%20move%20up%20to%20Canada%20when%20we%20retire%2C%26quot%3B%20but%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-move-canada%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethey%20couldn't%20get%20a%20visa%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20fellow's%20a%20Ph.D.%20and%20a%20really%20smart%20technical%20guy%20%E2%80%94%20and%20his%20wife%20is%20pretty%20bright%2C%20too.%20They%20couldn't%20get%20a%20visa%20because%20they%20were%20simply%20too%20old.%20Once%20you're%20%E2%80%94%20let's%20say%2050%20%E2%80%94%20the%20immigration%20system%20disadvantages%20you.%20They%20have%20a%20merit-based%20point%20system%20and%20start%20worrying%20about%20things%20like%20age.%20That's%20the%20thinking.%20Once%20you%20reach%20a%20certain%20age%2C%20or%20if%20you%20don't%20have%20certain%20other%20legs%20up%2C%20the%20criteria%20by%20which%20you%20can%20get%20a%20working%20visa%20is%20stacked%20against%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%5BIn%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.canada.ca%2Fen%2Fimmigration-refugees-citizenship%2Fservices%2Fimmigrate-canada%2Fexpress-entry%2Fcheck-score%2Fcrs-criteria.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECanada's%20Comprehensive%20Ranking%20System%20(CRS)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20rates%20potential%20immigrants%20based%20on%20age%2C%20language%20fluency%2C%20education%2C%20professional%20expertise%2C%20and%20if%20you%20have%20a%20Canadian%20partner%20%E2%80%94%20applicants%2045%20years%20old%20or%20older%20receive%200%20points.%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhereas%20if%20you're%20a%20young%20guy%20just%20out%20of%20college%2C%20you%20have%20some%20reasonable%20skills%2C%20and%20you%20even%20know%20a%20few%20words%20of%20French%2C%20you%20probably%20wouldn't%20have%20a%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20ways%20around%20it%2C%20but%20if%20the%20expectation%20is%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20just%20going%20to%20go%20up%20there%20and%20apply%20for%20a%20visa%20and%20get%20a%20visa%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20may%20not%20happen%20like%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2263102055-f98e-46a7-9095-671172e0d0de%5C%22%3EI%20needed%20a%20change%20from%20the%20cold%20and%20long%20nights%20in%20Canada%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20born%20in%20Stuttgart%2C%20Germany.%20When%20my%20parents%20and%20I%20moved%20to%20Canada%2C%20I%20was%20about%203%20and%20written%20into%20my%20parents'%20passports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20got%20their%20visas%20and%20eventually%20became%20naturalized%20Canadians%2C%20which%20was%20bestowed%20on%20me.%20So%2C%20for%20all%20practical%20purposes%2C%20I'm%20a%20Canadian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fraised-in-canada-live-in-us-life-better-in-us-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20Toronto%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20went%20to%20school%20in%20Toronto%2C%20and%20it%20wasn't%20until%20the%20early%20side%20of%20my%20career%20that%20I%20moved%20out%20into%20western%20Canada%20to%20Calgary%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-canada-from-us-differences-pros-cons-guns-drugs-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBritish%20Columbia%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20an%20engineering%20degree%20and%20an%20MBA%20%E2%80%94%20which%2C%20at%20that%20time%2C%20was%20a%20pretty%20good%20combination%20to%20earn%20a%20job%20and%20make%20a%20living.%20I%20looked%20at%20the%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3Eavailable%20jobs%20in%20the%20market%20and%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BGo%20to%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20where%20your%20skills%20will%20be%20valued%20the%20most.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20applied%20to%20a%20couple%20of%20things%20and%20got%20a%20call%20one%20day.%20It%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BAre%20you%20interested%20in%20coming%20down%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20said%20yeah%2C%20and%20there%20I%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20needed%20warmer%20weather%2C%20and%20I%20was%20able%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20Canada's%20long%20winter%20nights.%20The%20summers%20in%20Canada%20were%20great%20%E2%80%94%20you%20could%20golf%20at%2011%20p.m.%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20winters%20were%20awful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeasonal%20affective%20disorder%20really%20got%20to%20me.%20It's%20not%20so%20much%20the%20cold%20as%20the%20long%20winter%20nights.%20It's%20dark.%20My%20wife%20says%20I%20had%20started%20hibernating%2C%20so%20I%20wanted%20to%20leave%20that%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e17d7ad5-e881-4e13-a385-282bb59f3c3e%5C%22%3EI%20rented%20in%20the%20US%20and%20bought%20a%20home%20in%20Canada%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20moved%20to%20the%20US%2C%20I%20found%20that%20if%20I%20pushed%20myself%2C%20I%20could've%20bought%20a%20house%2C%20but%20I%20kept%20holding%20off.%20I%20found%20it%20easy%20to%20rent%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20affordable.%20I%20could%20get%20by%20without%20any%20problem.%20What%20I%20didn't%20put%20into%20a%20mortgage%2C%20I%20put%20into%20stocks%20and%20stuff%20like%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20lived%20there%20for%20almost%2030%20years%20in%20two%20or%20three%20residences.%20I%20paid%20about%20%243%2C200%20monthly%20in%20Los%20Altos%20Hills%2C%20California%2C%20right%20by%20Stanford%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20came%20close%20to%20buying%20a%20couple%20of%20times%2C%20but%20the%20property%20tax%20burden%20in%20California%20is%20significantly%20higher%20than%20what%20you%20would%20find%20in%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20buy%20a%20house%20in%20California%20for%20%243%20million%2C%20you're%20looking%20at%20%2440%2C000%20yearly%20in%20property%20taxes.%20%3Cem%3E%5BZillow%20estimates%20a%20%243%20million%20home%20in%20Santa%20Clara%20County%20would%20cost%20%2436%2C300%20annually%20in%20property%20taxes.%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%20I%20could%20go%20on%20a%20trip%20for%20six%20months%20on%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20did%20the%20same%20thing%20in%20Toronto%2C%20I%20might%20spend%20between%20%246%2C000%20and%20%248%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that's%20a%20big%20difference.%20%3Cem%3E%5BAccording%20to%20the%20city%20of%20Toronto%2C%20a%20%243%20million%20home%20costs%20%2421%2C459%20in%20city%2C%20education%2C%20and%20building%20fund%20taxes.%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20moved%20back%20to%20Canada%20about%2015%20years%20ago.%20My%20father%20was%2096%20then%2C%20and%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BLet's%20go%20back.%26quot%3B%20My%20wife%20is%20Canadian%2C%20and%20we%20have%20family%20up%20here.%20We%20settled%20in%20and%20bought%20our%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20a%20summer%20home%20up%20north%20in%20the%20lake%20country.%20It's%20not%20bad%2C%20but%20it%20gets%20cold%20in%20the%20winter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20ever%20move%20back%20to%20the%20US%2C%20my%20preference%20is%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanadian-boomer-its-not-easy-becoming-a-dual-citizen-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fd