ation%20that%20came%20out%20of%20the%20Fed's%20latest%20meeting%20could%20impact%20how%20much%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwill-mortgage-rates-go-down-this-year%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emortgage%20rates%20go%20down%20next%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20if%20they%20drop%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20meeting%20featured%20new%20economic%20projections%2C%20including%20the%20Fed's%20famed%20%26quot%3Bdot%20plot%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20chart%20showing%20where%20Fed%20policymakers%20think%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-the-federal-funds-rate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20funds%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20go%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20previous%20set%20of%20economic%20projections%2C%20policymakers%20were%20anticipating%20four%20rate%20cuts%20in%202025.%20But%20in%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreserve.gov%2Fmonetarypolicy%2Ffiles%2Ffomcprojtabl20241218.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDecember%20projections%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20now%20only%20foresee%20two%20cuts%20next%20year.%20They%20also%20expect%20inflation%20to%20take%20longer%20to%20reach%20their%202%25%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22367f3210-e175-45f6-a5a7-46e4f3a4b06a%5C%22%3EWhat%20fewer%20Fed%20cuts%20mean%20for%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Faverage-mortgage-interest-rate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20aren't%20directly%20impacted%20by%20changes%20to%20the%20federal%20funds%20rate%2C%20they%20are%20expected%20to%20ease%20in%202025%20as%20the%20Fed%20continues%20lowering%20its%20benchmark%20rate.%20So%20what%20does%20it%20mean%20that%20the%20Fed%20may%20now%20make%20fewer%20cuts%20than%20expected%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20near%20term%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20are%20likely%20to%20move%20a%20bit%20higher.%20And%20they%20may%20only%20drop%20slightly%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMortgage%20investors%20now%20are%20demanding%20higher%20yields%20because%20of%20the%20change%20in%20expectations%20for%20growth%20in%20inflation%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Emanuel%20Santa-Donato%2C%20senior%20vice%20president%20and%20head%20of%20the%20capital%20markets%20team%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftomo.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETomo%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223862a354-6918-47ed-9df8-6f04a8fb54d2%5C%22%3EInflation%2C%20the%20Fed%2C%20and%20uncertainty%20around%20the%20next%20administration%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20possible%20the%20Fed%20won't%20even%20be%20able%20to%20get%20those%20two%20anticipated%20cuts%20in%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERodney%20Ramcharan%2C%20an%20economist%20and%20professor%20of%20finance%20and%20business%20economics%20at%20the%20USC%20Marshall%20School%20of%20Business%2C%20thinks%20those%20cuts%20are%20unlikely%20to%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reason%20is%20that%20inflation%20remains%20above%20the%20target%2C%20the%20incoming%20administration%20is%20likely%20to%20pursue%20an%20inflationary%20program%2C%20which%20can%20add%20another%20maybe%2020%20to%2030%20basis%20points%20to%20inflation%2C%26quot%3B%20Ramcharan%20says.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it's%20difficult%20to%20see%20how%20and%20where%20those%20cuts%20are%20going%20to%20come%20from.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20economists%20have%20flagged%20certain%20policy%20proposals%20from%20President-elect%20Donald%20Trump%20as%20potentially%20inflationary%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-what-to-buy-business-customers-anticipation-nervous-prices-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparticularly%20his%20proposed%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20inflation%20starts%20rising%20in%20response%20to%20the%20new%20administration's%20policies%2C%20the%20Fed%20may%20opt%20to%20keep%20rates%20steady.%20Or%2C%20it%20could%20be%20forced%20to%20raise%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFed%20officials%20have%20said%20that%20they%20believe%20inflation%20will%20continue%20to%20come%20down%2C%20though%20it%20may%20take%20longer%20than%20initially%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERamcharan%20says%20it's%20difficult%20to%20know%20where%20inflation%20will%20go%2C%20and%20that%20it's%20possible%20the%20Fed%20will%20need%20to%20raise%20rates%20next%20year%20to%20combat%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20with%20uncertainty%20and%20the%20volatility%20of%20the%20incoming%20administration%20is%20that%20it%20then%20causes%20economic%20policy%20to%20whip%20back%20and%20forth%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a4e52573-a30f-4a89-b5d7-bdc607858947%5C%22%3EWhat%20does%20this%20mean%20for%20homebuyers%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%20for%20homebuyers%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20probably%20won't%20drop%20enough%20to%20substantially%20improve%20affordability%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20market%20is%20not%20forecasting%20any%20material%20decline%20in%20mortgage%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Santa-Donato.%20%26quot%3BSo%20from%20a%20homebuyer's%20perspective%2C%20there%20really%20isn't%20any%20reason%20to%20wait%20for%20interest%20rates%20to%20decline%20any%20more.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESanta-Donato%20notes%20that%20many%20forecasters%20predict%20mortgage%20rates%20will%20hover%20around%20the%20mid-6%25%20range%20next%20year.%20For%20reference%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2F30-year-mortgage-rates%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E30-year%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20at%206.60%25%20last%20week%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freddiemac.com%2Fpmms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFreddie%20Mac%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%